A Strong Number is a number whose sum of the factorial of its digits is equal to the number itself.

For example:

145 → 1! + 4! + 5! = 1 + 24 + 120 = 145 → Strong Number

123 → 1! + 2! + 3! = 1 + 2 + 6 = 9 → Not a Strong Number

Write a program to check whether a given number is a Strong Number or not.

Input Format

A single positive integer N.

Constraints

Print "Strong Number" if the number is a strong number, otherwise print "Not a Strong Number".

Output Format

1 ≤ N ≤ 10⁶

Sample Input 0

144
Sample Output 0

Not a Strong Number

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
#include <stdio.h>
#include <string.h>
#include <math.h>
#include <stdlib.h>

    int fun(int n){
    int fact=1;
    for(int i=2;i<=n;i++)
        fact=fact*i;
    return fact;
    }
    
int main()
{
   int n,ans=0;
   scanf("%d",&n);
   int t=n;
   while(t){
    ans += fun(t%10);
    t=t/10;
  }
   if(n==ans)
     printf("Strong Number");
   else
     printf("Not a Strong Number");

   return 0;
}

